n ins Zentrum stellen, versuchen andere »Fremdheit« zu dekonstruieren. Janosch Freuding zeigt Möglichkeiten auf, diese unterschiedlichen Auffassungen aufeinander zu beziehen, und wirkungsvoll gegen Othering-Strukturen in interreligiöser Bildung vorzugehen.  afunded by Erzbistum Bamberg  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aFremdheit. 4aInterkulturalität. 4aOrdnung. 4aOthering. 4aPostkolonialismus. 4aRassismus. 4aReligion. 4aReligionssoziologie. 4aReligionswissenschaft. 4aSubjektorientierung. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aForeignness.  aInterculturalism.  aOrder.  aOthering.  aPostcolonialism.  aRacism.  aReligion.  aReligious Studies.  aSociology of Religion.  aSubject Orientation.2 aErzbistum Bambergefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022z9783110994537oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2022z9783111025094oZDB-23-TGP0 cprintz978383766043240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839460436?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839460436zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839460436/original  a978-3-11-076700-1 DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-TGPb2022